article.headline: Texas-Pan American survives Tennessee Tech 81-78
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Shaquille Boga made a half-court shot with no time on the clock to lift Texas-Pan American to a thrilling 81-78 win over Tennessee Tech Friday night. Texas-Pan American (2-2) led the whole second half until Josiah Moore scored off a Javorn Farrell turnover with 46 seconds to play to make 78-78. Tennessee Tech (1-2) had a chance to win, but turned the ball over with five seconds to play. Inbounding from the backcourt, Boga had to put up a shot with time expiring and made it from half-court to pull out the win. Farrell led all scorers with 23 points for Texas-Pan American. Boga had 17 and Justin Leathers added 14 to go along with 12 rebounds. Ladon Carter had 17 points off the bench to lead Tennessee Tech. It was the opening game of the Holiday Inn Downtown Marina Islanders Tournament.
